{"title": "How Do I Configure My Practice to Automatically Submit Medicare Claims?", "body": "When this settings is enabled, the system will automatically transmit any claims in the \"Unclaimed Amount\" section at the close of business to Medicare, provided that the patient's Health Identifying information (OPV, OVV, PVF) has been successfully validated.\nTo turn on this feature, follow these steps:\nGo to More\nSelect Settings\nSelect Configuration Settings.\nSelect your practice name\nGo to Claiming-PRODA. Check the box for Automatically Submits Medicare Claims. \nClick Save\nNote: Automatically submitting claims specifically relates to Bulk Billing, DVA and PCI. Patient claims, like Bill to Patient and Bill to Head of Family are sent to Medicare in real time.\n  How Do I Configure My Practice to Automatically Retrieves Medicare Report?"}